---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="dreams"
  description="dreams index / active imagination, dream symbols, inner dialogue, nightmares, shadow projection"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">dreams / archive wing / index</div>
    <h1>dreams</h1>
    <p>
      dream life, symbolic images, inner dialogue, and the hidden movement of the psyche.
      not random noise, but living material that can be read, felt, and worked with.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      this wing gathers pages on dream process, projection, and the ways the unconscious
      speaks through image, repetition, and emotional charge.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">entry sequence</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <div class="grid-links">
        <a href="/dreams/active-imagination">
          <span class="link-title">active imagination</span>
          <span class="link-desc">dialogue with inner figures, image work, conscious encounter.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/dreams/dream-symbols">
          <span class="link-title">dream symbols</span>
          <span class="link-desc">what a dream is, image logic, and symbolic language.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/dreams/inner-dialogue">
          <span class="link-title">inner dialogue</span>
          <span class="link-desc">conversation with inner voices and figures.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/dreams/nightmares">
          <span class="link-title">nightmares</span>
          <span class="link-desc">fear dreams, intensity, and confrontation.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/dreams/shadow-projection">
          <span class="link-title">shadow projection</span>
          <span class="link-desc">emotion, projection, and hidden material.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">how to read</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p>
        dreams do not speak in straight explanation. they speak through image, mood,
        repetition, exaggeration, inversion, and symbol. the point is not to flatten
        them into a single meaning too quickly.
      </p>
      <p>
        read slowly. notice what returns. notice what disturbs you, what fascinates you,
        and what feels strangely important. often the dream image that makes the least
        sense at first carries the most energy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">dreams map</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p><a href="/dreams/active-imagination" class="link-blue">active imagination</a> — conscious encounter with inner images</p>
      <p><a href="/dreams/dream-symbols" class="link-red">dream symbols</a> — symbolic language and image logic</p>
      <p><a href="/dreams/inner-dialogue" class="link-green">inner dialogue</a> — inner voices and dialogue</p>
      <p><a href="/dreams/nightmares">nightmares</a> — fear, intensity, confrontation</p>
      <p><a href="/dreams/shadow-projection">shadow projection</a> — projection and hidden material</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">note</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p class="muted">
        this section will expand as the archive grows, but these pages form the first working path.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>